<span id="xiv.iii.xxviii"></span>

<span id="xiv.iii.xxviii-p1"></span> <span class="c4"><span
id="xiv.iii.xxviii-p1.1"></span>Canon XXVII.</span>

<span id="xiv.iii.xxviii-p2"></span><span class="sc"><span
id="xiv.iii.xxviii-p2.1"></span>None</span> of those who are in the
catalogue of the clergy shall wear clothes unsuited to them, either
while still living in town or when on a journey:  but they shall wear
such clothes as are assigned to those who belong to the clergy.  And if
any one shall violate this canon, he shall be cut off for one week.

<span id="xiv.iii.xxviii-p3"></span><span class="sc"><span
id="xiv.iii.xxviii-p3.1"></span>Ancient Epitome of Canon XXVII.</span>

<span id="xiv.iii.xxviii-p4"></span>*A clergyman must not wear an
unsuitable dress either when travelling or when at home.  Should he do
so, he shall be cut off for one week.*

